GCP buckets can be accessed via multiple types of authorities.One such option is &#39;Service Account&#39; i.e. 
If we have service account with desired permissions than we can access the GCP resources. Snowflake uses the service account mechanism for GCP interaction.

**Service Account Creation**: To create a service account,we need to create an 

    Integration object in Snowflake.
    CREATE STORAGE INTEGRATION GCS_INT
    TYPE = EXTERNAL_STAGE
    STORAGE_PROVIDER = GCS
    ENABLED = TRUE
    STORAGE_ALLOWED_LOCATIONS=(&#39;gcs://my-bucket-name01/&#39;)
    STORAGE_BLOCKED_LOCATIONS=(&#39;gcs://mybucket1/path1/sensitivedata/&#39;);

Describe the Integration and note the service account ID. It will be a column in the integration.

    DESC STORAGE INTEGRATION GCS_INT;

**CREATE the data format**:

    CREATE OR REPLACE FILE FORMAT MY_CSV_FORMAT TYPE = CSV;

**Create the intermediate stage**

    CREATE STAGE MY_GCS_STAGE URL = &#39;gcs://my-bucket-name01/&#39; 
    STORAGE_INTEGRATION = GCS_INT  FILE_FORMAT = MY_CSV_FORMAT;

**List the stage**: Verify the created stage is there or not.
	

    LIST @MY_GCS_STAGE; 

**Snowflake Create Table**

    CREATE TABLE EMPLOYEE(NAME VARCHAR, CLASS VARCHAR,DORM VARCHAR, ROOM 
    VARCHAR, GPA VARCHAR);

**Execute Copy command**:
	

    COPY INTO EMPLOYEE FROM @MY_GCS_STAGE PATTERN=&#39;employee-.*[.]csv&#39;;
	
**Verify the Snowflake table result**:
	

    SELECT * FROM EMPLOYEE;

